benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags - Retrieve bundle tags

covered: Valid requests / happy paths: successful 200 responses for default and combinations of query parameters (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05).
Empty response handling: scenario for bundles with no tags returns an empty JSON array (TC06).
Path parameter validation & errors: invalid UUID -> 400 and not-found -> 404 covered (TC08, TC07).
Query-parameter robustness: tests for invalid audit values, unexpected query params, injection attempts and regression for includedDeleted behavior (TC09, TC10, TC14, TC17).
Authentication basics & errors: missing and invalid authentication token cases -> 401 covered (TC12, TC13).
Resilience and non-functional scenarios: API unavailable, slow dependencies, very large result sets, concurrency and resource-utilization/performance tests are present (TC11, TC15, TC16, TC19, TC20).
Regression/backward-compatibility checks: explicit regression tests for deleted-tags handling and default/no-audit behavior (TC17, TC18).
Content-Type assertion present in at least one happy path (TC01).
gaps: Pagination: No tests for pagination semantics, page/limit params, Link headers or paging behavior with large datasets (GUIDELINE: Pagination).
Caching behavior: No tests assert ETag, Cache-Control, If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since or 304 Not Modified behavior (GUIDELINE: Caching Behavior).
Rate limiting / throttling: No explicit tests for 429 responses, Retry-After header or throttling under sustained load (GUIDELINE: Rate Limiting).
Authorization granularity: No tests for 403 Forbidden / role-based access (authenticated but unauthorized users).
Schema/contract-level validation: Tag object field-level checks (required fields, types) and explicit audit-object schema for FULL vs MINIMAL vs NONE are not asserted.
Query-parameter edge cases: invalid boolean values for includedDeleted, explicit audit=NONE, blank bundleId or borderline UUID-like values, and malformed query-value semantics are not covered.
Response headers & consistency: Content-Type is only asserted in one scenario; other headers (Cache-Control, ETag, Link, rate-limit headers) are not validated across responses.

Error response contract: Tests check for an error message but do not validate structured error schema (error codes, type, correlation id) or server-error (500) handling beyond degraded dependency simulations.
recommendations: Add pagination tests: page/limit offsets, Link headers, total-count/metadata and requests for pages beyond available data; include performance with paged responses.
Add caching tests: verify ETag and Cache-Control headers, verify 304 Not Modified via If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since and repeatable responses with cache headers.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests: generate sustained/high-frequency requests to validate 429 responses, Retry-After header and client behavior when limits are exceeded.
Add authorization-role tests: verify 403 Forbidden for authenticated but unauthorized users and validate owner/tenant restrictions if applicable.
Add schema/contract validation: use JSON Schema to assert Tag object fields/types and audit object contents for FULL vs MINIMAL vs NONE; include negative cases for missing/extra fields.
Cover query-param edge cases: test invalid boolean values for includedDeleted (e.g., text), explicit audit=NONE, blank or borderline UUIDs, very long parameter values and malformed query strings.
Assert response headers consistently: add checks for Content-Type, Cache-Control, ETag and any API-specific headers in all successful and error scenarios.

Add error-response contract and server-failure tests: validate structured error payloads for 4xx/5xx, test 500 on backend failures, and ensure correlation ids/logging hooks are present for observability.
